The current year has opened well, withtrading prospects remaining favourable, Burmah Oil Co Plc&lt;BURM.L> said in a statement with its 1986 results.    The company plans to maintain a steady rate of investmentin its marketing operations and to obtain improved profitmargins on its liquified natural gas, LNG, project.    Burmah has the financial capacity to continue makingacquisitions within its business sectors, it added. Therationalisation programme, including sale of the Bahamas oilterminal and all peripheral activities, is now complete.    Pre-tax profit for 1986 rose to 105.9 mln stg from 79.6mln.REUTER^M&#3;